<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-103] Log4jLogEvent proxies ThrowableProxy objects</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-103</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While verifying &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-99&quot; title=&quot;MapRewritePolicy always behaves like mode &amp;quot;Add&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-99&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-99&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I stumbled across another small issue:&lt;br/&gt;
When a Log4jLogEvent is reconstructed (in AsynchAppender, MapRewritePolicy or PropertiesRewritePolicy) the ThrowableProxy of the original LogEvent is used to construct the new Log4JLogEvent.&lt;br/&gt;
There the ThrowableProxy is proxied again. During this the package resolution is repeated (mostly  with slightly different result).&lt;br/&gt;
I created a patch for Log4JLogEvent to reuse existing ThrowableProxy objects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Best Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Das&lt;/p&gt;</description>
